#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!CDarkGreen  #!Rsmd Selecting, 
Moving, and Deleting Tool Icons #!N #!EC #!N #!N To select 
a tool icon, click on it. #!N #!N To select a 
group of tool icons, use one of these methods: #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N o Hold down the Shift 
key and click on each tool icon in turn. #!N #!I30 
#!N o Position the cursor on the canvas near a corner 
of the group and drag the mouse to draw a selection 
box around the tool icons you want. To select the tool 
icon, you must completely enclose it in the selection box. As 
a tool icon is encompassed by the selection box, it is 
highlighted (indicating that it is selected). #!N Note: If you have 
tools selected already and you want to select more, hold down 
the Shift key and either click on a single icon, or 
drag the selection box over several icons to select them. To 
select all icons on the canvas, use the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Select All 
#!EF option of the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF pull-down menu. #!N #!N 
#!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N To deselect an icon, shift-click 
on it. #!N #!N To deselect a group of tools, use 
one of these methods: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 
#!N o Shift-click on each icon. #!N #!I30 #!N o Shift-drag 
to draw a box around the tools you want to deselect. 
As a selected tool is encompassed in the box, it becomes 
unhighlighted. Release the button to deselect the tools. #!N #!I0 #!N 
#!EF #!N #!N Note: Clicking on an empty part of the 
canvas deselects all selected tools. #!N #!N #!N To move a 
tool icon: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. 
Press and hold the left mouse button on the tool icon 
and drag it to the desired location. While you are dragging 
the tool, an outline of the tool icon follows the motion 
of the mouse, but the tool icon remains in the original 
location. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Release the mouse button at the 
desired location. The tool icon moves to that location. Any lines 
connecting to other tools are rerouted to the tool's new location. 
#!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N To move a group 
of tool icons: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 
1. Select a group of tool icons to be moved. #!N 
#!I30 #!N 2. Position the cursor on any member of the 
group and drag it. An outline of each tool icon follows 
the motion of the mouse. #!N #!I30 #!N 3. Release the 
mouse button. The icons representing the tools move to the new 
location. Any affected connections are rerouted. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N 
#!N #!N To delete tool icons: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N 
#!N #!I30 #!N 1. Select the tool icon or group to 
be deleted. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Press the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ctrl+Delete #!EF 
accelerator key or click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Delete #!EF option of 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF menu. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N 
